import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['X'], data['Y'])
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['X'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='X')
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Y'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Y')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Series'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Series'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Series'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['Series'], data['X'])
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('X')
    plt.title('What is the trend of X over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['X'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='X', by='Series', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Series and X?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('X')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Series', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
